{"id": 243235990, "title": "Huge collection of talent gathers for Canada Basketball training camp with one absence", "text": "But as Barrett explained it, the Golden State Warriors made a late call to change those plans. \u201cWell, for us, Andrew was fine. We were talking to him consistently. He\u2019s been training for weeks and weeks getting ready for this. And then I got a call from Golden State a day or two before camp saying that they\u2019re holding him out,\u201d Barrett said. \u201cSo, from what I see, this is not an Andrew decision. This is from the team. And so he won\u2019t be with us.\u201d A request for comment from the Warriors to Postmedia late Friday was not immediately returned. Wiggins, the son of former NBA player Mitchell Wiggins and ex-olympian Marita Payne-Wiggins, had talked on a recent media tour of being excited to get the opportunity to head to Paris. \u201cMost of all, I\u2019m disappointed for him. I think, he\u2019s gone through a lot the last couple of years,\u201d Barrett said of Wiggins, who has battled injuries as well as dealt with personal matters. \u201cAnd then obviously his mother was an Olympian. This is something he (was) looking forward to and working towards and really on the uphill climb \u2026 especially ending the season last year.", "summary": "It wasn&#8217;t Avengers assemble, but the most talented collection of Canadian basketball players ever gathered in one place was pretty impressive to see in downtown Toronto on Friday. Canada&#8217;s senior men&#8217;s team is returning to the Olympics this summer for the first time since 2000 and superstar guards Shai Gilgeous-Alexander (the NBA MVP runner-up) and [&#8230;]", "url": "https://torontosun.com/sports/basketball/nba/toronto-raptors/huge-collection-of-talent-gathers-for-canada-basketball-training-camp-with-one-absence", "image": "https://smartcdn.gprod.postmedia.digital/torontosun/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/1671642841-scaled-e1694457285272.jpg?quality=100&strip=all",